== Betting investigation ==
{{Main|2025 Turkish football betting scandal}}

As part of an investigation conducted by the Istanbul Chief Public Prosecutor's Office, known to the public as the “Football Betting Investigations,” Elmalı's name was included after it was discovered that he had placed bets on a legal betting platform. Due to his involvement, Elmalı was removed from [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]'s squad.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Elmali removed from Türkiye squad as 1,024 players face betting investigation |url=https://www.turkiyetoday.com/sports/elmali-removed-from-turkiye-squad-as-1024-players-face-betting-investigation-3209733 |access-date=2025-11-11 |website=[[Türkiye Today]]}}</ref>

Elmalı admitted to betting on a match that did not involve his own team five years ago.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-10 |title=TFF hangi futbolcuları bahis oynamakla suçladı, şimdi ne olacak? |url=https://www.bbc.com/turkce/articles/cgjdpqeel93o |access-date=2025-11-11 |website=[[BBC News Online]] |language=tr}}</ref> On 13 November, the Turkish Professional Football Disciplinary Committee (PFDK) imposed a ban on Eren Elmalı, preventing him from playing football for 45 days.<ref>{{Cite web |title=PFDK Kararları - 13.11.2025 - PFDK Kararları TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=246&ftxtID=49006 |access-date=2026-05-01 |website=www.tff.org}}</ref>

